1
00:00:20,411 --> 00:00:22,326
Good to be back?

2
00:00:22,370 --> 00:00:24,067
Almost like the old days?

3
00:00:24,111 --> 00:00:26,504
Right? Remember
that spot uptown?

4
00:00:32,293 --> 00:00:36,384
No! No! No, no!

5
00:00:36,427 --> 00:00:37,515
Stay with me!

6
00:00:37,559 --> 00:00:40,083
Allen, please! No!

7
00:00:40,127 --> 00:00:43,565
No! No, no, no, no!

8
00:00:56,317 --> 00:00:58,667
What do we got?Drive-by shooting.

9
00:00:58,710 --> 00:01:00,364
Witnesses said it looks
like tonight's headliner,

10
00:01:00,408 --> 00:01:02,366
Cameron Gooding,
was the intended target,

11
00:01:02,410 --> 00:01:03,628
but his driver
got hit instead.

12
00:01:03,672 --> 00:01:04,847
Cameron Gooding?

13
00:01:04,890 --> 00:01:07,197
Cameron Gooding?

14
00:01:08,329 --> 00:01:10,331
You two?

15
00:01:10,374 --> 00:01:12,811
What, you're the only two
detectives in all of New York?

16
00:01:12,855 --> 00:01:14,639
Right place,
right time.

17
00:01:14,683 --> 00:01:16,424
Unlike your driver,
apparently.

18
00:01:16,467 --> 00:01:17,816
My friend.

19
00:01:17,860 --> 00:01:19,122
You sure
he wasn't the target?

20
00:01:19,166 --> 00:01:20,384
No way.

21
00:01:20,428 --> 00:01:21,994
He was always the good guy.

22
00:01:22,038 --> 00:01:24,345
Always got us home
at the end of every night.

23
00:01:25,563 --> 00:01:27,913
No, them bullets
were for me.

24
00:01:27,957 --> 00:01:29,393
Any idea who would
want you dead?

25
00:01:29,437 --> 00:01:30,916
Could be anyone.

26
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:33,180
Maybe it was Playa Boy Shine.

27
00:01:34,355 --> 00:01:36,357
He called Playa Boy Shine out

28
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,662
on his most recent album.

29
00:01:37,706 --> 00:01:40,012
We made amends.

30
00:01:40,056 --> 00:01:42,102
What about after your scandal
broke? Any threats then?

31
00:01:42,145 --> 00:01:43,407
Some.

32
00:01:43,451 --> 00:01:45,844
Maybe you might want
to stop playing coy with us

33
00:01:45,888 --> 00:01:48,282
so we can figure out
who the hell it was

34
00:01:48,325 --> 00:01:49,892
that killed
your supposed friend.

35
00:01:49,935 --> 00:01:51,328
Don't you say another word!Well, maybe

36
00:01:51,372 --> 00:01:53,417
you should say a word
and stop holding out!

37
00:01:53,461 --> 00:01:55,680
Allen was a good guy!
He didn't deserve this!

38
00:01:56,725 --> 00:01:58,509
It's all my fault.

39
00:02:01,295 --> 00:02:03,035
That should be me!

40
00:02:04,211 --> 00:02:06,778
That should be me.

41
00:02:09,999 --> 00:02:11,305
Thank you again for agreeing

42
00:02:11,348 --> 00:02:12,697
to be a part
of our panel.

43
00:02:12,741 --> 00:02:15,309
Of course. Any time.

44
00:02:16,397 --> 00:02:18,355
A.D.A. Reagan, do
you have a minute?

45
00:02:18,399 --> 00:02:20,836
Sure. You have
some more policy suggestions

46
00:02:20,879 --> 00:02:23,230
you want me to pass on
to the D.A.?

47
00:02:23,273 --> 00:02:25,188
Sorry. I know I can
be a little...

48
00:02:25,232 --> 00:02:26,407
Outspoken?

49
00:02:26,450 --> 00:02:28,148
No worries.

50
00:02:28,191 --> 00:02:31,412
You remind me a lot of myself
when I used to go here.

51
00:02:31,455 --> 00:02:33,501
Ramona Lewis.

52
00:02:33,544 --> 00:02:35,416
Nice to meet you.Likewise.

53
00:02:35,459 --> 00:02:36,982
Yeah, I studied a
lot of your cases.

54
00:02:37,026 --> 00:02:39,202
Your career at the D.A.'s office
is something I aspire to.

55
00:02:39,246 --> 00:02:41,857
Well, we should talk about
you coming in for an interview.

56
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:44,599
Actually, I had a
different kind of favor.

57
00:02:46,557 --> 00:02:48,994
My best friend was murdered
a couple months ago.

58
00:02:49,038 --> 00:02:51,606
I'm sorry. Here in New York?

59
00:02:51,649 --> 00:02:55,305
She got involved with this cult
led by this guy Daniel Shapiro.

60
00:02:55,349 --> 00:02:57,394
And she killed herself
shortly after.

61
00:02:57,438 --> 00:02:59,614
I thought you said
she was murdered.

62
00:02:59,657 --> 00:03:00,919
Might as well have been.

63
00:03:00,963 --> 00:03:02,443
Shapiro convinced her
to take her own life.

64
00:03:02,486 --> 00:03:05,010
And your office tried to
charge him with manslaughter.

65
00:03:05,054 --> 00:03:06,534
Tried and failed.

66
00:03:06,577 --> 00:03:08,318
Well, if it's already
been investigated,

67
00:03:08,362 --> 00:03:10,277
there's not much
I can do to help.

68
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:12,583
Then who knows how many
more lives he's gonna ruin.

69
00:03:13,715 --> 00:03:18,067
Please, A.D.A. Reagan,
just review the case.

70
00:03:18,110 --> 00:03:20,156
Her name was Yelena Page.

71
00:03:22,376 --> 00:03:24,291
I'll look into it.

72
00:03:24,334 --> 00:03:26,336
No promises.

73
00:03:31,646 --> 00:03:33,213
Sergeant?Boss.

74
00:03:33,256 --> 00:03:34,562
How's the apartment?

75
00:03:34,605 --> 00:03:36,477
Feels more like home
every day, sir, thank you.

76
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:38,043
Good. Means a lot.

77
00:03:38,087 --> 00:03:40,132
I wanted to talk to you
about a rookie

78
00:03:40,176 --> 00:03:42,570
I assigned to your squad
last week-- Sarah Brooks.

79
00:03:42,613 --> 00:03:44,049
Yeah, came in with a
chip on her shoulder,

80
00:03:44,093 --> 00:03:45,442
but we'll make a
good cop of her yet.

81
00:03:45,486 --> 00:03:47,009
I don't doubt it.

82
00:03:47,052 --> 00:03:49,316
Um, I see she's already earned
herself a command discipline.

83
00:03:49,359 --> 00:03:51,622
Yeah, I visited her on post
to scratch her memo book,

84
00:03:51,666 --> 00:03:54,190
but she said she'd
forgotten it in her locker.

85
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:56,540
Little harsh, isn't it?

86
00:03:56,584 --> 00:03:59,326
Attention to detail
is the heart of good policing.

87
00:03:59,369 --> 00:04:00,762
Don't start with the
platitudes, Reagan.

88
00:04:00,805 --> 00:04:02,633
It was her first
week on patrol.

89
00:04:02,677 --> 00:04:03,852
I'm a little confused, boss.

90
00:04:03,895 --> 00:04:05,201
You've always wanted me
to run a tight ship.

91
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:07,812
Yes, but there is such a
thing as too firm a hand.

92
00:04:07,856 --> 00:04:10,554
Don't see how this was too firm.
It's all by the book.

93
00:04:10,598 --> 00:04:12,643
I wanted your side,
and I have it,

94
00:04:12,687 --> 00:04:14,689
but I'm ripping up the rip.

95
00:04:18,693 --> 00:04:19,911
End police violence now!

96
00:04:19,955 --> 00:04:21,478
All right, folks,
let's give them some space.

97
00:04:21,522 --> 00:04:23,480
Guys, I'm just trying
to get my kids to school.

98
00:04:23,524 --> 00:04:25,265
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Get McKenzie off the force!

99
00:04:25,308 --> 00:04:26,440
Please, let us get through.

100
00:04:26,483 --> 00:04:27,702
- Excuse me. Excuse me.
- Daddy!

101
00:04:27,745 --> 00:04:29,704
You should be
ashamed of yourself!

102
00:04:29,747 --> 00:04:30,835
Guys, please, please!

103
00:04:30,879 --> 00:04:33,316
Racist cops!All right, all right.

104
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,622
Daddy!

105
00:04:34,665 --> 00:04:36,624
Leave my kids alone!

106
00:04:36,667 --> 00:04:39,453
End police violence now!
End police violence now!

107
00:04:39,496 --> 00:04:40,715
End police violence now!

108
00:04:40,758 --> 00:04:44,109
End police violence now!
End police vi...

109
00:04:45,110 --> 00:04:46,851
It's been like this
since yesterday.

110
00:04:46,895 --> 00:04:48,940
This ain't right.

111
00:04:52,509 --> 00:04:54,555
Someone found
his home address.

112
00:04:54,598 --> 00:04:55,860
What's patrol doing?

113
00:04:55,904 --> 00:04:58,167
Everything they can,
which isn't a lot.

114
00:04:58,210 --> 00:04:59,647
And what's that mean?

115
00:04:59,690 --> 00:05:00,952
Means you can't
use much force

116
00:05:00,996 --> 00:05:03,520
defending a cop accused
of excessive force.

117
00:05:03,564 --> 00:05:05,522
Operative word... "accused."

118
00:05:05,566 --> 00:05:07,350
Which used to
mean something.

119
00:05:07,394 --> 00:05:09,396
"Accused" has been
replaced with "convicted"

120
00:05:09,439 --> 00:05:11,354
down in ye olde
public square.

121
00:05:11,398 --> 00:05:14,618
What happened? Did you eat
your Wheaties this morning?

122
00:05:14,662 --> 00:05:16,707
I just think that things have
gotten out of hand.

123
00:05:16,751 --> 00:05:18,579
Thank you.

124
00:05:18,622 --> 00:05:19,884
Welcome to our world.

125
00:05:19,928 --> 00:05:21,364
Pardon me, Sid,
but I'm usually

126
00:05:21,408 --> 00:05:22,844
the voice of reason
in your world.

127
00:05:22,887 --> 00:05:24,846
But when IAB,
the Bronx D.A.

128
00:05:24,889 --> 00:05:26,761
and the Civilian
Complaint Review Board

129
00:05:26,804 --> 00:05:29,111
all find no evidence
of criminality

130
00:05:29,154 --> 00:05:30,939
on Detective McKenzie's part...

131
00:05:30,982 --> 00:05:32,244
The potato keeps getting passed

132
00:05:32,288 --> 00:05:33,768
until they find someone
who will.

133
00:05:33,811 --> 00:05:35,291
And they've done
exactly that.

134
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:37,772
NYPD Administrative Judge
John Bradshaw informs us...

135
00:05:37,815 --> 00:05:41,950
His ruling on the McKenzie case.

136
00:05:41,993 --> 00:05:43,952
But that's good, right?
He's our guy.

137
00:05:43,995 --> 00:05:45,214
He says

138
00:05:45,257 --> 00:05:46,607
McKenzie's actions may have

139
00:05:46,650 --> 00:05:48,652
violated department guidelines.

140
00:05:48,696 --> 00:05:49,827
Why the hell
would he say that?

141
00:05:49,871 --> 00:05:52,613
One doesn't always make
one's bones

142
00:05:52,656 --> 00:05:55,311
by going along
with the establishment.

143
00:05:55,355 --> 00:05:58,140
People tend to change
when the spotlight's on them,

144
00:05:58,183 --> 00:05:59,794
and he just grabbed it.

145
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:01,970
You think

146
00:06:02,013 --> 00:06:04,233
our own guy
would hammer McKenzie?

147
00:06:04,276 --> 00:06:08,498
If our own guy
is now maybe his own guy.

148
00:06:08,542 --> 00:06:10,544
Yeah.

149
00:06:38,615 --> 00:06:41,662
A.D.A. Flynn really dropped
the ball on this Shapiro case.

150
00:06:41,705 --> 00:06:43,968
- What'd you find?
- A real botch job.

151
00:06:44,012 --> 00:06:46,797
It's like he opened the
milk, took one bad whiff,

152
00:06:46,841 --> 00:06:48,190
put it back in the fridge.

153
00:06:48,233 --> 00:06:50,627
Guess it's a good thing
he's no longer with us.

154
00:06:50,671 --> 00:06:52,890
I'll say. He missed allegations
of a pyramid scheme,

155
00:06:52,934 --> 00:06:55,458
dropped domestic
violence complaints,

156
00:06:55,502 --> 00:06:58,113
missing persons reports
from worried parents.

157
00:06:58,156 --> 00:07:00,942
You're saying Shapiro's
been kidnapping these girls?

158
00:07:00,985 --> 00:07:03,901
They usually turn up a couple of
weeks later, refusing to talk.

159
00:07:03,945 --> 00:07:05,903
I mean, it's all
very spooky.

160
00:07:05,947 --> 00:07:08,210
You speak to anyone
in his cult?

161
00:07:08,253 --> 00:07:10,386
Yeah, I-I poked around their
little co-op in Brooklyn,

162
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,997
but they clammed up
when they realized who I was.

163
00:07:14,216 --> 00:07:15,522
You know, Ramona was right.

164
00:07:15,565 --> 00:07:17,045
We really failed her friend.

165
00:07:17,088 --> 00:07:18,699
Want to go after this guy?

166
00:07:18,742 --> 00:07:20,831
Yeah. But we're gonna need

167
00:07:20,875 --> 00:07:22,833
to get someone
in his circle to talk.

168
00:07:24,313 --> 00:07:27,316
I think I got just the
person for the job.

169
00:07:39,328 --> 00:07:41,504
Go.

170
00:07:46,422 --> 00:07:48,424
Expecting that 49 later today,
Sergeant.

171
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:49,730
Yes, sir, I'll get
it right to you.

172
00:07:53,037 --> 00:07:55,083
There a question
go with that look?

173
00:07:55,126 --> 00:07:57,477
No, sir.

174
00:07:57,520 --> 00:08:00,088
Good.

175
00:08:09,097 --> 00:08:10,664
What's up?

176
00:08:10,707 --> 00:08:12,666
We're looking for Pia Toledo.
That's what's up.

177
00:08:12,709 --> 00:08:13,797
Who's looking?

178
00:08:13,841 --> 00:08:15,712
Well, I'm Mister Rogers,

179
00:08:15,756 --> 00:08:16,974
and this is my neighborhood,

180
00:08:17,018 --> 00:08:18,541
so answer
the question.

181
00:08:18,585 --> 00:08:19,586
Where's Pia Toledo?

182
00:08:24,939 --> 00:08:27,550
- Pia Toledo?
- Who the hell are you?

183
00:08:27,594 --> 00:08:30,205
I'm Detectives Reagan.
This is Detective Baez.

184
00:08:30,248 --> 00:08:32,337
And you can wait outside.

185
00:08:36,603 --> 00:08:38,213
What's with the muscle?

186
00:08:38,256 --> 00:08:40,258
You worried about
some sort of retribution?

187
00:08:40,302 --> 00:08:42,217
I don't know about that shooting
if that's why you're here.

188
00:08:42,260 --> 00:08:44,654
Gooding allegedly assaulted you.

189
00:08:44,698 --> 00:08:46,830
And from what we heard,
your career pretty much ended

190
00:08:46,874 --> 00:08:48,223
after the scandal broke.

191
00:08:48,266 --> 00:08:50,442
Yeah, I got blacklisted.

192
00:08:50,486 --> 00:08:52,880
Labeled as one of those girls
sleeps her way to the top.

193
00:08:52,923 --> 00:08:54,577
Nice world we live in?

194
00:08:54,621 --> 00:08:56,797
But that doesn't mean
I tried to kill him.

195
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,494
We went through his phone
and found

196
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,670
you'd sent him a slew
of threats-- death threats.

197
00:09:00,714 --> 00:09:03,630
You've never heard of hyperbole?
A rapper's bread and butter?

198
00:09:03,673 --> 00:09:06,720
Okay. Where were you
two nights ago at 11:30 p.m.?

199
00:09:06,763 --> 00:09:08,765
Asleep... in this room.

200
00:09:08,809 --> 00:09:11,115
And is there anyone
who can verify that for you?

201
00:09:11,159 --> 00:09:12,595
Wouldn't you like to know.

202
00:09:12,639 --> 00:09:14,728
The hotel's got
cameras, don't they?

203
00:09:14,771 --> 00:09:16,730
Yeah, and we plan
on taking a look at them.

204
00:09:16,773 --> 00:09:18,209
In the meantime, you worked

205
00:09:18,253 --> 00:09:20,734
with Dead Dove Records
for a long time.

206
00:09:20,777 --> 00:09:22,692
Can you think of anyone else
in Cameron Gooding's universe

207
00:09:22,736 --> 00:09:23,998
who might want to see him dead?

208
00:09:24,041 --> 00:09:25,216
Most of those players left.

209
00:09:25,260 --> 00:09:26,696
Why is that?

210
00:09:26,740 --> 00:09:28,655
After his business partner
went to prison,

211
00:09:28,698 --> 00:09:30,787
Gooding ran Dead Dove Records
right into the ground.

212
00:09:30,831 --> 00:09:33,224
You're saying
the record label is broke?

213
00:09:33,268 --> 00:09:34,748
Yep, and so is he.

214
00:09:34,791 --> 00:09:38,447
Word is, he owes all
sorts of unsavory types.

215
00:09:38,490 --> 00:09:39,796
- Like who?
- I don't know.

216
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:42,669
But I'm telling you,
the king is dead.

217
00:09:43,844 --> 00:09:45,759
Figuratively speaking.

218
00:09:48,892 --> 00:09:50,590
I know you've been
undercover before,

219
00:09:50,633 --> 00:09:52,113
but this ain't
a one-time op.

220
00:09:52,156 --> 00:09:53,593
We want you to go deep.

221
00:09:53,636 --> 00:09:54,681
I'm ready.

222
00:09:54,724 --> 00:09:56,639
Are you? I mean,
you're ready to adapt,

223
00:09:56,683 --> 00:09:58,119
to improvise,

224
00:09:58,162 --> 00:10:00,164
to stay in character even
if there's a gun to your head?

225
00:10:00,208 --> 00:10:01,905
- Well, I think so.
- You see...

226
00:10:01,949 --> 00:10:04,125
if you hesitate like that,
you'll be made in a second.

227
00:10:04,168 --> 00:10:06,823
Lucky for you,
you got me to teach you.

228
00:10:06,867 --> 00:10:08,695
They used to call me
"the Chameleon."

229
00:10:10,740 --> 00:10:13,090
This is Ramona Lewis.

230
00:10:13,134 --> 00:10:16,398
She brought the case to Erin,
and Yelena Page,

231
00:10:16,441 --> 00:10:18,400
her best friend
who offed herself,

232
00:10:18,443 --> 00:10:21,708
thanks to this guy--
Daniel Shapiro, the ringleader.

233
00:10:21,751 --> 00:10:24,798
He runs a supposed
wellness group

234
00:10:24,841 --> 00:10:26,800
based upstate and in Brooklyn.

235
00:10:26,843 --> 00:10:29,672
We've identified a girl
we think is a weak link.

236
00:10:29,716 --> 00:10:33,371
We'd like you to go undercover
and get her to open up.

237
00:10:33,415 --> 00:10:35,286
Is Shapiro dangerous?

238
00:10:35,330 --> 00:10:37,767
We think so. There's been,
several disappearances

239
00:10:37,811 --> 00:10:38,899
around him.

240
00:10:38,942 --> 00:10:41,162
Evidence suggests
he maintains control

241
00:10:41,205 --> 00:10:44,165
over these girls through
violence and sexual coercion.

242
00:10:44,208 --> 00:10:46,733
Gifts that he may very well try
to share with you.

243
00:10:46,776 --> 00:10:48,822
Still think you're up to this?

244
00:10:49,910 --> 00:10:51,433
I'm ready.

245
00:10:57,569 --> 00:10:58,832
We noticed you...

246
00:10:58,875 --> 00:11:01,095
One second.

247
00:11:01,138 --> 00:11:03,053
Do you mind?

248
00:11:04,881 --> 00:11:06,404
As I was saying,

249
00:11:06,448 --> 00:11:08,755
we noticed you haven't canceled
any of your tour dates yet.

250
00:11:08,798 --> 00:11:09,843
Why not?

251
00:11:09,886 --> 00:11:11,366
I'm not about to
be intimidated.

252
00:11:11,409 --> 00:11:12,715
Or maybe you're just
so strapped for cash,

253
00:11:12,759 --> 00:11:14,499
you can't afford
to take a day off?

254
00:11:14,543 --> 00:11:16,318
- What are you talking about?
- Dead Dove's...

255
00:11:16,327 --> 00:11:17,764
