542
00:23:00,117 --> 00:23:01,380
And now you've done it twice.

543
00:23:01,423 --> 00:23:02,946
What exactly are you implying?

544
00:23:02,990 --> 00:23:04,295
I'm not implying anything.
I'm just pointing out a fact.

545
00:23:04,339 --> 00:23:06,167
Here's a fact:
you question me on this again,

546
00:23:06,210 --> 00:23:08,082
and it won't be
a rookie getting the rip.

547
00:23:08,125 --> 00:23:09,300
You hear me?

548
00:23:10,345 --> 00:23:11,564
Loud and clear.

549
00:23:23,445 --> 00:23:27,710
My father wasn't arrested,
but he left me, too.

550
00:23:27,754 --> 00:23:30,234
I struggled with it
for a long time.

551
00:23:30,278 --> 00:23:33,237
After I met Daniel,
everything changed.

552
00:23:33,281 --> 00:23:35,065
Daniel Shapiro, right?

553
00:23:35,109 --> 00:23:37,067
Yeah.
What's he like?

554
00:23:37,111 --> 00:23:38,199
He's great.

555
00:23:38,242 --> 00:23:41,115
A brilliant mind
and the most open heart.

556
00:23:41,158 --> 00:23:43,030
He founded this group

557
00:23:43,073 --> 00:23:44,597
