I'm dedicating
the show tonight to Allen.

781
00:35:36,395 --> 00:35:37,396
You're still going on?

782
00:35:37,439 --> 00:35:38,484
Hell, yeah.

783
00:35:38,527 --> 00:35:39,702
And you two
are coming out with me

784
00:35:39,746 --> 00:35:41,487
so I can thank you
in front of everybody.

785
00:35:41,530 --> 00:35:44,011
Well, we-we...
No, we appreciate that,

786
00:35:44,054 --> 00:35:46,100
but we can't.
We have paperwork to do.

787
00:35:46,144 --> 00:35:47,536
You sure?

788
00:35:47,580 --> 00:35:49,190
You could help me open up.

789
00:35:49,234 --> 00:35:50,844
I know you know all the lyrics.

790
00:35:52,715 --> 00:35:55,109
In another lifetime.

791
00:36:06,512 --> 00:36:07,643
So, when do you leave?

792
00:36:07,687 --> 00:36:10,168
Day after tomorrow.I hear the rent's

793
00:36:10,211 --> 00:36:12,518
even higher in San Francisco
than it is here.

794
00:36:12,561 --> 00:36:13,519
Is that even possible?

795
00:36:13,562 --> 00:36:14,607
What are you
complaining about?

796
00:36:14,650 --> 00:36:16,696
You got the hookup
from your CO.

797
00:36:16,739 --> 00:36:18,698
I'll be living in one of
the economically challenged

798
00:36:18,741 --> 00:36:20,395
neighborhoods
I'm helping, so rent

799
00:36:20,439 --> 00:36:22,005
will be manageable.

800
00:36:22,049 --> 00:36:23,572
You know which one yet?

801
00:36:23,616 --> 00:36:25,226
The start-up's putting me up
while I sort out

802
00:36:25,270 --> 00:36:26,793
- a place to stay.
- I'm hoping it will be...

803
00:36:26,836 --> 00:36:28,534
near public transportation.

804
00:36:28,577 --> 00:36:29,970
- I would think so.
- Which is what...

805
00:36:30,013 --> 00:36:31,363
exactly, in San Francisco?

806
00:36:31,406 --> 00:36:33,669
One of those, 
Rice-A-Roni cable cars?

807
00:36:33,713 --> 00:36:35,323
Do you have any friends there?

808
00:36:35,367 --> 00:36:37,717
a couple from school,
but it'll be an adjustment.

809
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:39,153
A big adjustment.

810
00:36:39,197 --> 00:36:41,503
I mean, you have to
find a new bagel shop.

811
00:36:41,547 --> 00:36:42,635
New pizza parlor.

812
00:36:42,678 --> 00:36:44,114
And bacon, egg and cheese
on a roll.

813
00:36:44,158 --> 00:36:45,377
I hear they close

814
00:36:45,420 --> 00:36:46,508
the bars early, too.

815
00:36:46,552 --> 00:36:47,640
- Hey.
- What?

816
00:36:47,683 --> 00:36:48,945
I was 22 once.

817
00:36:48,989 --> 00:36:50,164
Okay.

818
00:36:50,208 --> 00:36:52,166
I get it, guys.
It's not New York.

819
00:36:52,210 --> 00:36:54,168
Nicky, I think what
everybody's trying to say

820
00:36:54,212 --> 00:36:57,215
is congratulations
on landing a new job.

821
00:36:58,781 --> 00:37:00,348
No small feat these days.

822
00:37:00,392 --> 00:37:03,003
Well, thank you.What if you don't like it?

823
00:37:03,046 --> 00:37:05,440
Then she will move back and
live with her dear old mom

824
00:37:05,484 --> 00:37:07,007
till the end of her days.

825
00:37:07,050 --> 00:37:08,661
You'd hate that
more than I would.

826
00:37:08,704 --> 00:37:09,662
True.

827
00:37:09,705 --> 00:37:10,663
Hey, Francis and I

828
00:37:10,706 --> 00:37:11,838
get along fine.

829
00:37:11,881 --> 00:37:13,100
Don't we?

830
00:37:14,144 --> 00:37:15,450
Kinda.

831
00:37:15,494 --> 00:37:16,843
So, now that it's

832
00:37:16,886 --> 00:37:19,715
actually happening,
are you more nervous or excited?

833
00:37:19,759 --> 00:37:21,935
Honestly, it's hard to say.

834
00:37:21,978 --> 00:37:23,545
When I was in Boston,
I'd walk the streets

835
00:37:23,589 --> 00:37:25,417
to keep my mind and my feet
moving. Made me less homesick.

836
00:37:25,460 --> 00:37:26,461
I didn't miss New York

837
00:37:26,505 --> 00:37:27,767
'cause I never left,

838
00:37:27,810 --> 00:37:30,335
which is the secret to
my long and happy life.

839
00:37:30,378 --> 00:37:31,379
Right.

840
00:37:31,423 --> 00:37:32,902
I missed New York so much,

841
00:37:32,946 --> 00:37:35,557
we had Nathan's hot dogs
shipped all the way to Fallujah.

842
00:37:35,601 --> 00:37:37,646
I think, for me,
it was calling my mom

843
00:37:37,690 --> 00:37:39,257
maybe every other day.

844
00:37:39,300 --> 00:37:41,694
Subtle.

845
00:37:41,737 --> 00:37:43,086
A stack of Madmagazines
at summer camp.

846
00:37:43,130 --> 00:37:45,132
What?You got bored sometimes.

847
00:37:45,175 --> 00:37:46,264
Baseball.

848
00:37:46,307 --> 00:37:47,352
- Baseball?
- Yeah, I always

849
00:37:47,395 --> 00:37:49,005
traveled with two gloves
and a ball.

850
00:37:49,049 --> 00:37:51,007
It was easy to scare up
a game of catch.

851
00:37:51,051 --> 00:37:53,793
Took me home to my own backyard.

852
00:37:53,836 --> 00:37:55,882
What about you, Nicky?

853
00:37:55,925 --> 00:37:59,494
Is organizing a Sunday potluck
too on the nose?

854
00:38:01,017 --> 00:38:03,585
Wow, I sense the makings
of a new tradition.

855
00:38:03,629 --> 00:38:05,283
Yeah.

856
00:38:11,985 --> 00:38:13,943
Sure, come right in.

857
00:38:13,987 --> 00:38:15,728
Since day one, you've been
protecting Officer Brooks,

858
00:38:15,771 --> 00:38:17,469
- giving her special treatment.
- Be very careful

859
00:38:17,512 --> 00:38:18,861
what you say next, Reagan.

860
00:38:18,905 --> 00:38:20,167
You got a relationship with her,
one that's not

861
00:38:20,210 --> 00:38:21,342
strictly professional.

862
00:38:21,386 --> 00:38:23,736
More careful than that.

863
00:38:26,695 --> 00:38:28,088
You went to IAB?

864
00:38:28,131 --> 00:38:29,742
No.

865
00:38:29,785 --> 00:38:33,049
Look, Reagan,
I'm not sure what it is

866
00:38:33,093 --> 00:38:34,442
you think
you know...

867
00:38:34,486 --> 00:38:38,794
Officer Brooks's father was FDNY
and died on 9/11.

868
00:38:38,838 --> 00:38:41,275
He was also the best man
at your wedding.

869
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:43,669
You conducted
your own investigation?

870
00:38:43,712 --> 00:38:46,280
I was afraid I'd turn up
something worse.

871
00:38:51,720 --> 00:38:55,420
Sarah came up rough,
made a few bad decisions.

872
00:38:55,463 --> 00:38:58,814
I convinced her to take the
test, figured it would--

873
00:38:58,858 --> 00:39:02,427
hoped that it would help
straighten her out.

874
00:39:02,470 --> 00:39:05,604
Then you requested she be
put here, under your command.

875
00:39:05,647 --> 00:39:08,389
Under yours. I put her
on your squad because I knew

876
00:39:08,433 --> 00:39:10,826
you would be the best person
to get through to her.

877
00:39:12,959 --> 00:39:14,917
Why haven't you let me
do my job?

878
00:39:14,961 --> 00:39:17,485
If you're too harsh,
she'll cut and run.

879
00:39:17,529 --> 00:39:20,793
Then we drag her back here
kicking and screaming.

880
00:39:20,836 --> 00:39:21,968
But you're doing her no favors,

881
00:39:22,011 --> 00:39:23,709
letting her off the hook
every time.

882
00:39:23,752 --> 00:39:26,842
I guess I've got
a soft spot for her.

883
00:39:26,886 --> 00:39:29,932
All the more reason I should be
the one making the decisions.

884
00:39:31,934 --> 00:39:33,936
You're really growing
into those stripes, aren't you?

885
00:39:35,982 --> 00:39:37,853
That mean I can get back
to work?

886
00:39:38,898 --> 00:39:40,639
Why are you still standing here?

887
00:39:55,131 --> 00:39:57,133
I miss anything?

888
00:39:59,484 --> 00:40:02,748
I've always been able to count
on hockey to distract me.

889
00:40:02,791 --> 00:40:04,402
Moves so fast.

890
00:40:04,445 --> 00:40:06,360
Meaning it's not
working tonight?

891
00:40:08,841 --> 00:40:10,582
Did you try to talk him
out of it?

892
00:40:11,931 --> 00:40:13,498
I'm the guy who started
his troubles.

893
00:40:13,541 --> 00:40:16,892
You can't be both arsonist
and firefighter.

894
00:40:16,936 --> 00:40:19,242
Notifying IAB was
the right thing to do. You...

895
00:40:19,286 --> 00:40:21,462
The complaints had
to be investigated.

896
00:40:21,506 --> 00:40:23,421
I'm not so sure.

897
00:40:23,464 --> 00:40:24,857
It was by the book, Dad.

898
00:40:24,900 --> 00:40:28,426
What good's the book
if no one else is reading it?

899
00:40:29,470 --> 00:40:31,167
You don't mean that.

900
00:40:31,211 --> 00:40:34,519
Your doubts about your boss
could've been passed up to IAB,

901
00:40:34,562 --> 00:40:35,868
by the book.

902
00:40:35,911 --> 00:40:37,870
But you didn't.

903
00:40:39,785 --> 00:40:43,005
Because you see what I see.

904
00:40:43,789 --> 00:40:46,400
No, I just took a breath.

905
00:40:46,444 --> 00:40:48,402
No.

906
00:40:48,446 --> 00:40:52,101
You hit the brakes
because you're a smart guy

907
00:40:52,145 --> 00:40:55,278
in a careless time
when certain accusations,

908
00:40:55,322 --> 00:40:58,630
by their very nature,
carry a penalty

909
00:40:58,673 --> 00:41:02,982
the instant that accusation
is even whispered.

910
00:41:05,375 --> 00:41:06,725
Whether it has merit or not

911
00:41:06,768 --> 00:41:09,858
becomes utterly
beside the point.

912
00:41:12,905 --> 00:41:15,908
I'm glad I hit the brakes.

913
00:41:15,951 --> 00:41:18,867
So am I,

914
00:41:18,911 --> 00:41:23,002
and so is your boss,
I'm sure, but...

915
00:41:23,045 --> 00:41:26,962
going forward,
how the hell do we do our jobs?

916
00:41:27,006 --> 00:41:30,139
By learning from our mistakes,
like always.

917
00:41:30,183 --> 00:41:32,968
You remember 
"The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance"?

918
00:41:33,012 --> 00:41:34,404
Old movie?

919
00:41:34,448 --> 00:41:35,797
Yeah.

920
00:41:35,841 --> 00:41:38,365
This reporter's about to go
to press with a story

921
00:41:38,408 --> 00:41:40,541
based largely on bunk,

922
00:41:40,585 --> 00:41:43,936
and this other guy,
he challenges him.

923
00:41:43,979 --> 00:41:48,331
So the reporter says,
"This is the West, sir.

924
00:41:48,375 --> 00:41:53,336
When the legend becomes fact,
print the legend."

925
00:41:54,381 --> 00:41:56,644
So, like, forget
about the real facts?

926
00:41:57,689 --> 00:42:00,779
We got a version
of that going on.

927
00:42:01,823 --> 00:42:02,911
So, what do we do?

928
00:42:04,652 --> 00:42:07,307
I don't know.

929
00:42:09,439 --> 00:42:11,964
I don't know.

930
00:42:12,007 --> 00:42:14,923
But I do care.

